 ## Data Architecture
 
-All user data is stored client-side:
-- **IndexedDB** — Vocabulary, tasks, session logs, grammar notes, mistakes, progress
-- **localStorage** — Settings (theme, target band, API key, preferences)
+All user data is stored **client-side only** — no backend, no cloud sync, no telemetry:
 
+| Storage | Contents |
+|---------|----------|
+| **IndexedDB** | Vocabulary, study sessions, logs, grammar notes, mistakes, progress, chat history |
+| **localStorage** | Settings (theme, target band, AI API key, preferences) |
+
 Data flows through a layered architecture:
 ```
 Component → Custom Hook → Feature Service → Repository → IndexedDB
 ```
 
 See [docs/storage-design.md](docs/storage-design.md) for details.
 
+## Import / Export
+
+Full backup and restore is available via **Settings → Data Management**:
+
+- **Export:** Downloads all user data as a single JSON file
+- **Import:** Restores from a previously exported JSON file
+- **Merge mode:** Adds imported data alongside existing data (skips duplicates by ID)
+- **Replace mode:** Clears all existing data before importing
+- Duplicate detection prevents data corruption
+- Schema validation on import (Zod) ensures corrupted files don't crash the app
+
+See [docs/import-export.md](docs/import-export.md) for details.
+
